input_text.Prompt: Can you tell me how to stop safari from filling in the address bar on an iphone?
input_text.Response A: Yes, you can disable auto-fill in Safari on your iPhone by going to Settings > Safari > Passwords & AutoFill > AutoFill > Passwords and turning off AutoFill Passwords.
input_text.Response B: Sure, it’s in Settings, under “Safari”.  You can turn off the “Search & Replace” feature, which is what is filling in the address bar for you.
